quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  46,1,"Ḥā, Meem.{1}",footnotes:1:1
  46,2,"The revelation of the Book is from Allāh, the Exalted in Might, the Wise."
  46,3,"We did not create the heavens and earth and what is between them except in truth and [for] a specified term. But those who disbelieve, from that of which they are warned, are turning away."
  46,4,"Say, [O Muḥammad], "Have you considered that which you invoke besides Allāh? Show me what they have created of the earth; or did they have partnership in [creation of] the heavens? Bring me a scripture [revealed] before this or a [remaining] trace of knowledge, if you should be truthful.""
  46,5,"And who is more astray than he who invokes besides Allāh those who will not respond to him until the Day of Resurrection [i.e., never], and they, of their invocation, are unaware."